    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-pork-with-sesame-broccoli-and-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat. Once hot, add your<strong> mince</strong> (remove the paper if required) to the pan and cook for an initial 3 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-pork-with-sesame-broccoli-and-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> onion petals</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 3-4 min or until the mince is starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-pork-with-sesame-broccoli-and-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until tender</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-pork-with-sesame-broccoli-and-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince is starting to brown, add your<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Be careful \u2013 the garlic and ginger will sizzle from the heat of the oil</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>cornflour</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> Vietnamese-style mince</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-pork-with-sesame-broccoli-and-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of <strong>cooked long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave </strong>for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-pork-with-sesame-broccoli-and-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the broccoli is cooked, add your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for a final 30 secs \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame broccoli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-pork-with-sesame-broccoli-and-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with the<strong> Vietnamese-style pork</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>sesame broccoli </strong>to the side and season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
